enhanced_by.method_name: filteredIterator(Iterator<? extends E>, Predicate<? super E>)
enhanced_by.reason: Both methods use a predicate to filter or find elements in an iterator.
The find method can be used to verify the presence of an element before invoking indexOf, ensuring the iterator state is relevant.
The matchesAny method can be used to check if any element matches the predicate, which can be a precondition for indexOf.
